Gazprom, Rosneft, Globaltrans May Move: Russia Stock Preview

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-04-04T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/gazprom-rosneft-globaltrans-may-move-russia-stock-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 1.7 percent to 1,843.43.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX) and OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): President
 Dmitry Medvedev  instructed the government to start removing all
top state officials from the boards of public companies by Oct.
1 to improve the investment climate. Gazprom,  Russia ’s state gas
export monopoly, rose 2.6 percent to 235.07 rubles. Rosneft,
Russia’s biggest producer of crude, rose 1.4 percent in Moscow
to 263.89 rubles.  Globaltrans Investment Plc (GLTR)  : Russia’s largest non-
state rail operator will announce 2010 financial results. The
company’s global depository receipts rose 3.3 percent to $19 in
London trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
